File: The world athletics championships that were scheduled to take place in Eugene, Oregon, from 6 to 15 August 2021 can no longer be held on those dates. PARIS - The 2021 world athletics championships will be shifted to 2022 to accommodate the re-arranged Tokyo Olympics, World Athletics said. The announcement came immediately after Olympics organisers said the 2020 Tokyo Games -- postponed because of the coronavirus pandemic -- will now take place from 23 July to 8 August 2021. That means the world athletics championships that were scheduled to take place in Eugene, Oregon, from 6 to 15 August 2021 can no longer be held on those dates. READ: Postponed Tokyo Olympics to open 23 July 2021: organisers "We support the new 2021 dates for the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games announced today by the Japanese organisers and the IOC," World Athletics said in a statement. "This gives our athletes the time they need to get back into training and competition. "Everyone needs to be flexible and compromise and to that end we are now working with the organisers of the World Athletics Championships in Oregon on new dates in 2022 for our World Athletics Championships." Track and field is the traditional centrepiece of an Olympic Games.